@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

Playing with http apps gives me something to do to pass the time (eg lookup,
unrealaudio et al).

The previous URL grabbing source I had was thanks to rauper on #amiga (Nick
Loman), with modifications by Jeff Shepherd to get it working with gcc.

But now I've found a couple of generic unix C programs with source that do the
same thing, and I've included both of them here as well as compiled versions
(requiring ixemul43+).

[I also saw someone on csa.programmer wanting some URL grabbing source]

@ENDNODE

